Nigerian Cross River State, Essar Sign Power Deal, Guardian Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-06-03T07:58:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/nigerian-cross-river-state-essar-sign-power-deal-guardian-says.html
Nigeria ’s southern state of Cross
River signed a memorandum of understanding with Essar African
Holdings Co. to build a power plant, the Guardian reported,
citing the state’s deputy governor, Efiok Cobham.  The 600-megawatt plant will be built in two phases of 300
megawatts each, and work is expected to start within a year, the
Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 